def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    shape = [len(index.get_level_values(i).unique()) for i in clocs]

    # Performing unstack operation
    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs)

    # Check if the result is a Series
    if isinstance(unstacked, Series):
        unstacked = unstacked.to_frame()

    # Renaming the columns for multi-level index
    levels = index.levels
    new_levels = [levels[i] if i in clocs else [""]
                  for i in range(len(levels))]
    new_columns = MultiIndex.from_product(new_levels,
                                         names=[index.names[i]
                                           if i in clocs else None
                                           for i in range(len(levels))])

    unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
